 nonlinearity. An evaluation of available experimental phase\ndiagrams and first-principles free energies suggests mechano-chemical spinodal\ndecomposition should occur in metal hydrides such as ZrH$_{2-2c}$. The rich\nphysics that ensues is explored in several numerical examples in two and three\ndimensions and the relevance of the mechanism is discussed in the context of\nimportant electrode materials for Li-ion batteries and high temperature\nceramics.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 22 Aug 2015 01:02:11 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 28 Sep 2016 01:42:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-29"}
